          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thorium was separated from uranium ore. The final",
                "product was 91.32+-0.77 mg of thorium with a purity",
                "of 99.5+-1.2 wt%. Isotope ratio 230Th/232Th was",
                "determined by mass spectrometry to be 0.0922+-0.00150.",
                "In experiment a target stack  was used to degrade beam",
                "energy. Stack consisted of",
                "  - thin tantalum cover foil 5 mu-m thick",
                "  - ThO2 target with thickness ranging from",
                "    921.710+-0.005 to 1913.309+-0.005 mu-g Th/cm2 on",
                "    Ti backing (cover) 2 mu-m thick",
                "  - Y monitor foil",
                "  - spacer foil Ta (10 mu-m) or Pt (25 mu-m)",
                "  - ThO2 target on Ti backing",
                "  - spacer foil Ta (10 mu-m) or Pt (25 mu-m)",
                "  - ThO2 target on Ti backing",
                "  - Beam stop",
                "Together 8 target foils were irradiated. In first",
                "experiment stack with two target foils without spacers",
                "was used."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "90-TH-230",
